CatDescriptText: Cutline of related article published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 11, 1972, pg. 1 reads: "The Honorable Shirley Chisholm, candidate for the office of President, member of the Congressional Black Caucus and congresswoman form Brooklyn, N.Y., addressed a rally of Pittsburgh voters at Carnegie Music Hall, Sunday evening."Display ad published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 4, 1972, pg. 1 reads: "The public is invited to the rally and reception Sunday, March 5, 1972 - Rally at the Carnegie Music Hall 5p.m. - Reception at the Loendi Club 841 Ledlie Street 8 p.m."
TitMainTitle: Shirley Chisholm holding bouquet and standing with three women and three men, possibly in Loendi Club, for Presidential campaign rally
